5:
Lord Alk... I must ask you to become
my kaishakunin—and behead me.
13:
It has become painfully evident to
me in the past few days, particularly
after I assisted those lifeguards.
16:
Every action I take is nothing more
than an imitation. A farce—a game
of pretend, like those which children
play.
19:
And thus, no other choice remains
to me...
But to commit seppuku.
24:
You're going to have to help me
understand how you jumped to that
conclusion...
29:
You need not stress over the details,
Lord Alk. All I need is for you to
decapitate me. Strike the opening
between my head and torso.
33:
Um, how about NO! I'm not going to
cut your head off, Zantetsu!
37:
Hahaha. Do not fear; using this
specially engineered seppuku
device, the process is rendered
ENTIRELY safe!
40:
Once the system registers a signal
from both the abdomen and the
cervical vertebrae, it triggers a
period of blissful "post-puku" clarity.
45:
That's... just weird. And also probably
illegal! Who would even make
something like that?!
50:
So, basically, you're just depressed.
Am I right?
53:
Sounds like you need less
stomach-stabbing and more fun in
your life. Something to get your
mind off things.
60:
DAMN IT! Stupid damn machine just
ate up all my money! SCREW THIS
STUPID THING!
63:
WHOA, seriously? That dude in the
suit of armor's entered Fever mode
again!
66:
You're really on a roll here... I hate to
ask, but you're... not cheating or
anything, are you? Cause this is
incredible!
70:
Of course not! This is simply a game
of probability. Using my superior
processing speed, I'm able to easily
ascertain this machine's next moves.
79:
S-screw you! Do you have any idea
how much I lost?!
83:
Ah... How fruitless it all feels. No
matter how much I try to fill the void,
it remains empty. This isn't what I
truly desire...
87:
Damn, you're a natural at this, Mr.
Ninja Samurai!
90:
I get that it's all probability, but the
show you're putting on is something
else. It's enough to make some of
our top hackers blush!
93:
Say, how about you and I have
ourselves a face off? You look like
you're up for it.
97:
The hell's gotten into you?
Gambling? That's not your style.
101:
What can I say, I'm curious about
how he does things. I want to pick
apart his brain, so to speak.
105:
All you'll be picking apart is his
memories of takin' every last penny
you've got.
110:
C-come on, you don't know for sure
that I'm going to lose!
115:
A proper bout with a HERO from
Qualia City!
119:
This is the golden opportunity I've
been waiting for. I will gladly accept
your challenge!
127:
We'll be playing poker.
And you better not go easy on
me—cause I'll definitely be going all
out.
131:
I will bring my best to bear, as all
underdogs must do!
139: ...I'm all out. I've shot my last shot.
143:
Oh, what an electric, exhilarating
duel that was!
147:
If I hadn't lost my cool and gone all
in... I might have...
Ah, damn it all!
151:
I feel as if I discovered a brand new
side of you, Lady Bulleta. What a
fruitful glimpse into the mind of a
true hero!
155: Hero... You keep using that word...
159:
Why yes. Ever since coming to
Starview, I've immersed myself
thoroughly in all sorts of content
from Qualia City!
163:
This of course includes your great
oeuvre, Lady Bulleta!
165:
The bullet of freedom—a paragon
worthy of admiration! I am ever your
humble fan.
168:
If you would deign to humor one as
lowly as me, I would ask you to
regale me with tales of your life as a
HERO!
171:
What must I do to become a hero
such as you? Pray tell!
175:
Yeah, you're barking up the wrong
tree here.
178:
That's not me. I don't deserve to be
called a "hero"... There are plenty of
real heroes out there, but I'm not
one.
183:
No, no, no! That is not true! Ah, this
must be your refined humility
shining through again!
186: Think about it for a moment!
190:
You are Bulleta, the bullet of
freedom that pierced the skies. You
are a hero who changed the world!
194:
Yeah, that's definitely the narrative
King Jerkoff wants you to believe.
197:
...Just saying, but being that honest
and naive is likely to get you killed in
Qualia City.
200:
And you know what? From my
perspective, you're way more of a
hero than I am.
203:
What's got you so down anyway?
You're helping people, aren't you?
207:
Such is the self-evident duty of a
ninja samurai.
210:
That is why I do it. 
I... cannot say that my actions stem
from my own will.
213:
Both my mind and body are like
accessories, installed externally.
Given to me; not innate.
217:
Man. You and I couldn't be more
different.
220:
Qualia City's filled with heroes who
are just keeping up appearances.
Faking it. It's a marketing strategy,
really. Makes money.
223:
Way I see it, if you're actually worried
and thinking about it, you're already
better than most people out there.
238:
You're just so COOL, Lady Bulleta! I
am merely overwhelmed...
242:
You embody the very essence of a
HERO!
246: Sh-shut up! No I do not!
249:
All right, less talking, more walking.
Nimbus is waiting for us at the
restaurant.
252:
And by the way, you're paying, right?
That's a surefire way to get everyone
to think of you as their hero.
257:
Indeed! It is my duty to help out the
destitute and penniless among us!
Like you and Lord Nimbus.
261:
Throw some of that coin our way, Mr.
Ninja Samurai.
265:
I shall! Let us feast, drink, and greet
the dawn together!
